17/09/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The court of BiH confirmed on Thursday (September 16th) an indictment against Milivoje Cirkovic for crimes against humanity committed in 1995 at Srebrenica. 
The former Bosnian Serb police officer has confessed to killing a Bosniak civilian and according to local media reports has agreed to serve five years in prison as proposed by prosecutors. 
(RTRS, Srna, BHRT - 16/09/10)
